  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 2-month-old male infant is brought in for a health maintenance examination. He is growing and developing well. His height and weight are at the 50th percentile for his age, consistent with his previously documented growth parameters.\nHis head circumference is at the 90th percentile for his age, an increase from the 50th percentile at his newborn health examination. His head appears long and narrow, with a prominent occiput and a broad forehead. There are no dysmorphic features of his facies, and the remainder of his physical examination is unremarkable.\nWhich one of the following initial management approaches is most appropriate for this infant?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Reevaluation of head circumference in one month"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Referral to physical therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Referral to craniofacial specialists"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Increased time in the prone position while awake and monitored"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Referral for genetic testing"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Although head-circumference monitoring is important for all <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infants</a>, such monitoring alone is not adequate for an <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infant</a> who has had a substantial increase in head-circumference <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nn07Fg&anker=Z58c33debd1e5adfb39bb92898fbe05f6\" data-learningcard-id=\"nn07Fg\" data-anker=\"Z58c33debd1e5adfb39bb92898fbe05f6\" data-section-id=\"fpckKW0\" data-sememe-id=\"BDbzgD\">percentile</a> and is suspected of having <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-sememe-id=\"V50GQg\">craniosynostosis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"FZXgW9\">Physical therapy</span> referral is inappropriate for a child with suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-sememe-id=\"V50GQg\">craniosynostosis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>This patient's <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HJ0KvS&anker=Z5208bc2efbfd3c982ffbeacf78ebfcb3\" data-learningcard-id=\"HJ0KvS\" data-anker=\"Z5208bc2efbfd3c982ffbeacf78ebfcb3\">physical examination</a> findings are suggestive of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-sememe-id=\"V50GQg\">craniosynostosis</a>, a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vK0ARS&anker=Z42951d3ed62c1b6987f856e87d8e3c56\" data-learningcard-id=\"vK0ARS\" data-anker=\"Z42951d3ed62c1b6987f856e87d8e3c56\">skull</a> deformity that results from premature suture fusion. The long narrow shape of the head suggests <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Z51585d1fa315c88adab07fca103bc0ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Z51585d1fa315c88adab07fca103bc0ba\" data-section-id=\"8GYOaI\" data-sememe-id=\"GdaBrj\">scaphocephaly</a> in particular, which is the most common form of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-sememe-id=\"V50GQg\">craniosynostosis</a> and results from premature closure of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zbb1ba12f6b85ecbbb611c472382b629d\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zbb1ba12f6b85ecbbb611c472382b629d\" data-section-id=\"XT196T0\">sagittal</a> suture.<br><br>An <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infant</a> with suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-sememe-id=\"V50GQg\">craniosynostosis</a> should be referred to craniofacial specialists, ideally a multidisciplinary team that includes specialists from neurosurgery, plastic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a>, and oral and maxillofacial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a>.<br><br>Distinguishing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-sememe-id=\"V50GQg\">craniosynostosis</a> from more common <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z2eb72d2494721debd42b3e4d3e6b9bad\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z2eb72d2494721debd42b3e4d3e6b9bad\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">cranial</a> deformities is critically important to ensure appropriate management. <br><br><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kQ0mwf&anker=Z3a2bd6ef282973d6495c35cff504dbad\" data-learningcard-id=\"kQ0mwf\" data-anker=\"Z3a2bd6ef282973d6495c35cff504dbad\" data-section-id=\"A7XRoz\" data-sememe-id=\"baVHQG0\">Congenital muscular torticollis</a> is characterized by <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">lateral</a> neck <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Ze4037822f631cf13d894ef7837c90ad6\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Ze4037822f631cf13d894ef7837c90ad6\" data-section-id=\"M6cMlW0\">flexion</a> and rotation and can lead to plagiocephaly if left untreated. Referral to <span data-sememe-id=\"FZXgW9\">physical therapy</span> is recommended for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kQ0mwf&anker=Z3a2bd6ef282973d6495c35cff504dbad\" data-learningcard-id=\"kQ0mwf\" data-anker=\"Z3a2bd6ef282973d6495c35cff504dbad\" data-section-id=\"A7XRoz\" data-sememe-id=\"baVHQG0\">congenital muscular torticollis</a> that is severe or when home management has failed.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> The most appropriate initial care for an <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infant</a> with suspected isolated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-sememe-id=\"V50GQg\">craniosynostosis</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Z51585d1fa315c88adab07fca103bc0ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Z51585d1fa315c88adab07fca103bc0ba\" data-section-id=\"8GYOaI\" data-sememe-id=\"GdaBrj\">scaphocephaly</a>) involves referral to craniofacial specialists.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Positional plagiocephaly is characterized by flattening of the back or side of the head. It is caused by mechanical forces on the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vK0ARS&anker=Z42951d3ed62c1b6987f856e87d8e3c56\" data-learningcard-id=\"vK0ARS\" data-anker=\"Z42951d3ed62c1b6987f856e87d8e3c56\">skull</a>, often related to the position an <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infant</a> prefers when placed on his or her back to sleep. Regular repositioning for sleep — and time in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tg0XC2&anker=Z423422a74e138fb64d0150221926a76c\" data-learningcard-id=\"tg0XC2\" data-anker=\"Z423422a74e138fb64d0150221926a76c\" data-section-id=\"7O14FS0\" data-sememe-id=\"yobdeu\">prone position</a> when the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infant</a> is awake and being monitored (&quot;<span data-sememe-id=\"SaVyPG0\">tummy time</span>&quot;) — helps to strengthen the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infant</a>’s neck muscles and reduce pressure on the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vK0ARS&anker=Z42951d3ed62c1b6987f856e87d8e3c56\" data-learningcard-id=\"vK0ARS\" data-anker=\"Z42951d3ed62c1b6987f856e87d8e3c56\">skull</a>. <span data-sememe-id=\"FZXgW9\">Physical therapy</span> may also be indicated.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Referral for <span data-sememe-id=\"2E1TEi0\">genetic testing</span> may be appropriate at a later time but should not delay referral to craniofacial specialists. Fewer than 10% of cases of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g40FiT&anker=Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"g40FiT\" data-anker=\"Zba9edf09071740dd926783b89cdb84b2\" data-sememe-id=\"V50GQg\">craniosynostosis</a> are familial.</div>",
